<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.44.9-11_0001" />
<fw type="curatorial">9</fw>

<note type="curatorial">217-2</note>
<fw type="letterhead">
<hi rend="caps">UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI</hi>
<lb/>
<hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA</hi>
<lb/>

<hi rend="caps">COLLEGE OF ARTS AND SCIENCE</hi>
<lb/>
<hi rend="caps">DEPARTMENT OF ENGLISH</hi> </fw>   <opener><dateline>Oct. 20, '64</dateline>

<salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
</opener>
<p>One of these times I will send you some clippings and letters about the fine experience I had the day I visited Bancroft. These will do much to bring back the old days there when I was doing much of my best work.</p>
   
<p>The Garden Club of Bancroft is acquiring the little building I used as a study and will restore it. They've consulted me as to what needs to be done.</p>

<note type="authorial">(over)</note>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.44.9-11_0002"/>
<fw type="curatorial">10</fw>

<p>In a corner of the room in this little house I found a kitchen table that must be the one I used as a desk!!</p> 

<p>I do hope you are well and not working too hard.</p>

<p>Here are the old affectionate thoughts for you, dear Lady, and for Stewart. (I did want to have a good talk with him). And Bower? I'll hear about him through Dr. Kendrick if not direct.</p>

<p>I <hi rend="double underline">do</hi> wish you could have been in Bancroft with me!!</p>
<closer>
<salute>Always</salute> &#8212; <signed>John</signed>
</closer>

</div1>


